What is the structure of the data?¶

the data consists of 81 record for each loan, some of these data has null values and some has non-valuable data. These data is ranged between 2005 and 2014 with various characteristics of those loans. Out of these data there are 61 numeric variables and 20 objectis variables. I will work on 18 variables out of 18 and they are consisting of 5 discrete variables and 13 continuous variables.

What are the main features of interest in the dataset?¶

I am most interested to see the some data related to the borrowers such as income to dept ratio and what they can afford on monthly baseis. Also I want to investigate some data related to the loan it self such as Loan Origination Quarter, loan status, APR.

What features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your features of interest?¶

Iam not a sepcialest in this feild, but I expect that occupation and monthly income will affect the loan amount and its annual interest. There are a lot of data about the borrower, so I think by multivariant analysis these vaibales I could find intersting things.

Debt consolidation means combining more than one debt obligation into a new loan with a favourable term structure such as lower interest rate structure, tenure, etc. Here, the amount received from the new loan is used to pay off other debts.

  • Now Lets see what is borrower APR?

    APR is the annual cost of a loan to a borrower — including fees. Like an interest rate, the APR is expressed as a percentage. Unlike an interest rate, however, it includes other charges or fees such as mortgage insurance, most closing costs, discount points and loan origination fees.
